channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "Now, let's talk about what I consider one of the most important forms of communication in today's society. Although you may not know it, the texts that you send a girl after meeting her play a crucial role in deciding whether or not she's going to see you again. I never used to think texting really mattered, but then I realized how texting is like crack for girls. When I was in college, when T9 Word was the big rage with technology, I met this girl who would always text me. She was literally the only person I ever got texts from, and I would never respond and I'd just call her back. But she would never pick up. So finally, I just started replying to her texts, and every time we had a conversation, it would lead to sex. So that was 10 years ago, and now the crazy thing is, girls will literally think there's something wrong with you if you call them. We call it the Do Not Call Theorem. Here's the theorem. Every guy I know who is broke that wants my resources, as in my money, time, network, advice, etc., he calls me. I don't answer, and I text him back. Those with resources I want access to, I call. They don't answer, and text me back. Therefore, it follows that the person with resources texts the other person who wants his resources. To sum it up, he who doesn't have shit calls the dude that has shit. Without spending too much time on this, completely disregard any stupid girl advice that says, I just want a guy to call, because anyone that inflexible or subjective shouldn't be listened to. Nearly 99% of my girlfriends laugh about idiot guys who call them. If and when you call, you will appear desperate and needy. A text is preferred because it's the most efficient method of modern communication. So don't break social protocol here. Breaking social protocol too early will put you in a position to have to fight an uphill battle. In conclusion, do not call girls. You will look desperate. Here's one more secret. The best way to improve at texting is to have someone who is way better than you at it text for you. And that is exactly what happens when you join the Become a Social Genius group. Some guys aren't sure if they're getting love or interest from a girl they're texting. So here's a surefire way to tell. I call it the bubble test. Whoever has more bubbles and longer bubbles is more interested. The bubbles are the texts, the little blurbs that pop up on your phone. Your goal should be to have slightly less bubbles than she does. Let me show you an example. Here's a text thread with Jenny. She's on the left, I'm on the right. You can tell who's texting more. She's writing long sentences one after the other. At one point here she writes an entire novel and I'm writing just short replies. They're fun and flirty but she's investing way more in this text thread which is showing me and anyone who will look at it that she's into me and she's giving me way more love. She's in essence, she's chasing me. So I hope you enjoyed the video and stay tuned for the next one.
